    <text id="B0371T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McCutchen asks for advice from Jackson related to his appointment as County
                    Register, and notes that the estate of John McCutchen, a relative, will not be
                    settled for some time, as their is a claim against it by Henry Alexander.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Thos P Jackson <abbr expan="Assistant Agent">Asst
                        Agt</abbr> Bureau</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-06-01">June 1st 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Craigsville Augusta County <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I find that I have received the appointment of register at large for this county.
                    Be so kind as to inform me when I shall qualify as register &amp; before
                    whom and any suggestions you may make to me will be kindly received.</p>

                <p>I received yours of recent date and will say that the Estate of John <unclear>P.
                        W.</unclear> McCutchen will not be settled up for some time yet and you will
                    have time to investigate the validity of Henry Alexander's claim fully before it
                    is settled.</p>

                <p>hoping to hear from you by return mail</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am sir your most Obedient <abbr expan="Servant">Servt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>G.W. McCutchen</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
